Cesc Fabregas on a move to Real Madrid: &ldquo;There were a lot of talks with Florentino [Perez] &amp; [Ramon] Calderon. The first time, I was very young. I was 18 &amp; they offered me a big salary, but I felt like I belonged at Arsenal. Wenger had bet the farm on me. I couldn&rsquo;t leave.&ldquo; [AS]<br />
<br />
Fabregas: &ldquo;In any case, I&rsquo;ll always be grateful to Madrid for the way they treated me. When I was 23, I had a serious calf injury &amp; they sent me a really nice message. I&rsquo;m grateful for their interest in me but I always dreamed of playing for Barca. It all worked out pretty well.&rdquo;

Emery: &ldquo;As a player, it was very difficult to achieve some trophies. When I was starting as a coach, I was thinking, &lsquo;I want to progress, to improve, to move ahead&rsquo;, &amp; when the first title arrived, it was [a relief]. My objective is to achieve important things in football.&rdquo; #afc<br />
<br />
Emery: &ldquo;At the moment, I can be happy &amp; defend the Europa League because I think the UEFA people improve a lot this competition, but really, really, the first is the Champions League. My first trophy was the Europa League with Sevilla against Benfica in Turin. It was amazing.&rdquo;

Emery on his best moment at Arsenal: Says hard to pick one, but says the best moments are when we're playing at Emirates in front of supporters.<br />
<br />
Emery on the premier league: &quot;The most important league in the world.&quot;

Arsenal confirm that no international players have come back reporting any injuries<br />
